<Date>1610692494150</Date><rating>5< /rating>< text>
Lo and Behold... all who gather here under the domain of "Google Reviews" and hear my words, hear my chatter, HEAR... a story to be told. Gather round gather round as I unveil the story of Dr. Prero Orthodontics Magical Spa&Inn, a shining beacon of light in BEVERLY HILLS where some might even call it the "Heart of LOS ANGELES" whos profound skills run deeper than the migraine I'm giving an English Teacher with this Run-on sentence and grammatical anarchy...

(Note: this will be my 2nd telling of this story as the page collapsed on me and I lost the original review...Save your work people.)

It was a dew stricken morning for me in Shire-like residences of "Laurel Canyon", PEOPLE and terrain alike... When a travesty occurred in the midst of the evening. My Invisalign retainer, after three years of upper jaw bombardment...exploded with a thunderous crack right down the center. My lower jaw, unable to hold itself steady, pooled what seemed like an endless stream of hot magma breath and cheek scathing lava.

After some steady cleanup and panic, I zipped on over to Dr. google... who directed me to the wrong destination... but with a reputation held by one such as Dr. Prero, his colleagues gave me the number to his office...which I know refer to as "My 11th Home" (I'm quite the traveler you see) BUT A HOME NONETHELESS...

Upon scheduling an appointment, I trudged my way up the dastardly elevator to the 7th floor where his domain laid.... my nerves getting the best of me, I was outside in the sea of lung pandemic you see, my bones feeling the chill of the high peaks interior air conditioning! When... out of nowhere.. a saint appeared... whos eyes creased with glee behind a woven veil. "Do you have an appointment" she said. "You're **** right I do, please shelter me from this heathen air" I replied.

and so they did...

They brought me right in... and within minutes I found myself in a room filled with wonderful atmosphere and technological prowess of which the likes I'd never seen!!! I was swept off my feet by numerous Pegasi and graced upon a spine adjusting luxury lawn chair. Before I knew it, my mouth was being tenderly handled with such professionalism and care, that I could've had 32 root extracts done and I wouldn't even had known. In the lap of my handler, whos soft rubbery gloves graced my nutrients clobbers with so much love and compassion I cried tears of complete, and utter...joy.

It was upon my tears that Dr. Prero himself graced me with his presence. "Hello" he said with a voice of such man-li-tude that I felt my voice quake in comparison.
"I heard you needed a new retainer, don't worry... with our state of the art 3D imaging and processing power. We'll have your new dental dam to you within a few days. Not to mention... WE STORE YOUR IMAGES SO IF IT BREAKS AGAIN... YOU SIMPLY CALL AND GET A NEW ONE (take F****** note offices around the globe...cough cough).

My heart melted with such delight, that my only response was a esophageal gurgle coming from the back of my throat manifesting in physical form referred to as a "spit bubble". He nodded in approval.

I can't even begin to describe how little justice my words give the experience I felt at "Dr. Prero Orthodontics Magical Spa&Inn, a shining beacon of light in BEVERLY HILLS where some might even call it the "Heart of LOS ANGELES""....

I guess you'll just have to make an appointment and experience the magic yourself...

< text>
If you are looking for a friendly orthodontist with a proven history of reliability and excellence, Dr. Prero is the best choice. He gave me the smile I always wanted. My case was a little tricky initially because I required four extractions to create space for my bite. Obviously, this is not news anyone wants to hear. I was concerned the spaces would not close adequately and I would forever have four big holes in my smile. Dr. Prero assured me this was not the case and worked on closing the gaps quickly and effectively. Every appointment showed progress and kept me motivated to continue with his plan. I am very glad I trusted his professional judgment because today my smile is simply perfect! Everything went just as he said it would. Best of all, I had my braces off just in time for graduation as promised. I smiled really big in all my photos.

Some of Dr. Prero best qualities are his dedication to his work and patients. He takes his time evaluating your case. Most orthodontist will see you for only a minute, assign assistants something to do, and then tell you to return next month. Half the time they do not even know your name. This is not how Dr. Prero treats his patients. Dr. Prero maintains open communication throughout your treatment. He will ask how you feel and whether you have any questions or concerns. He talks with you about what he is doing and points out any problem areas he is targeting. He is professional and genuinely cares about helping you achieve the best smile possible. Believe me, this is hard to find. His ability to connect with patients and make them feel comfortable is truly unique. You will love Dr. Prero and be very thankful you chose him as your orthodontist.

If I had to do my treatment with Dr. Pero all over again I would. In fact, my younger sister just started her treatment with him earlier this year. There was no way we were going to let anyone else work on her smile. I am very excited to see her final results. Thank you Dr. Prero! You are the absolute best orthodontist!!!</text>

Well thursday night before memorial day weekend started two of my bottom two brackets broke and the wire was poking into my tongue and extremely painful. I had never had an issue with my retainers in the whole 8 years i have had them, till now. Just my luck my dentist isn't in on fridays, and the orthodontist that did my dental work is 3,000 miles away ( very unlucky and not helpful). So I began googling the best orthodontists in Beverly Hills praying I get helped Friday bc there was no way i would make it through the holiday weekend in that much pain and unable to chew solid food. After calling around 5-6 Orthodontists who were unable to accommodate me, Dr Prero's office told me that he would be willing to come back from his lunch break early to see me. I was so thankful.
Dr Prero was such a sweetheart. Very well educated and committed to making sure I was comfortable the whole time and happy every step of the way. He treated me like my happiness with his orthodontic work was the most important part of his day. He gave me all my options, we came up with a plan, and to my surprise he ended up giving me something even better then what I originally had done, which i didn't think was possible! He also answered all my questions, and gave me a very fair price which was a life saver since I have a broken foot and can't really work much right now. I almost wish I had more work that needed to be done bc his office and the whole experience with him was simply unbeatable.

<Rate>5< /Rate><Review>We used All Care Pet Clinic on May 05, 2019, after my Boxer had passed away.  Our regular Vet was closed for the weekend and they suggested on the voice greeting that we use them.

I called their office, devastated over the fact we just lost a member of our family.  Since this was our first pet death, I didn't know where to start or what to ask, but the person over the phone was very friendly and helpful.  She first asked when did I want to bring her in and they were more then accomidating with us wanting to bring her immediatly that afternoon.  They went over my options and prices over the phone for what we wanted her to have done.

We were asked to call when we arrived and they met us in the back of the building. They had us sign some paperwork and told us that they were sorry for our loss.

After all this was done and paid for, they even called my regular Vet who reached out to me to tell me how sorry they were that this happened.  I really appreicated that.

I would not only use them again for pet cremation, but would take my other fur babies to see them if our regular vet is ever closed.  All of their staff were super nice to me and even when I went to pick up my baby in her new box, they again said they were sorry for my loss.</Review>< Pics>

< Review>
I took my dog Bowser to All Care.  He was extremely sick from an unknown cause.  Rather than inundate me with tests (and their inherent costs), they did only what seemed like the most likely causal testing.  I was very sad and felt like this was "the end" for Bowser - that's how sick he was.  The doctor gave me several options (including euthanasia), but I elected to leave him there for the day on fluids and medications.  It is now almost two weeks later and Bowser is much better!  I don't know if he's "cured" for good (he IS 11 years old now), but his quality of life is much better and we feel better too knowing that he got the kind of care he needed and is with us for some time longer!  I am very grateful to the doctor and staff of All Care!  If your a pet owner like me, you fear taking your family member to a vet that you are unfamiliar with.  I can, with good conscious, tell you that you can rest assured that if you take your pet to All Care, you will not be broke and your pet will get excellent care!!< /Review>

< review>
When I first needed a mailbox, I first looked into the post office and considered it for the cheaper cost. The long lines and crowds were a turn-off so i decided to try UPS for 3 or 6 months first. I've been a customer now for about 2.5 to 3 years now and just renewed for another year. The main guy, Ryan, is always extremely helpful and take care of any package I send or receive. I even get a call when I get mail in so I don't have to stop by every day to check my empty box. A long as these guys keep doing what they do, I'll continue to keep doing business with them. Highly recommended.</review>

<Text>Shawn at Best Auto is impeccable!
I run a small overnight delivery business in far northern California. My business continues to grow at a rapid pace due to the global pandemic. Recently I doubled my workforce and was in need of solid, well priced vehicles in a short amount of time. The area in which I live has a limited selection of quality affordable vehicles. I exhausted my efforts purchasing vehicles locally. I was forced to search for vehicles outside of Humboldt county. Many fruitless searches finally led me to "Go Best Auto" sales in southern California. The vehicles looked to be in good shape according to the online photos and the prices were reasonable. Car prices were also in line with Kelly blue book, as well as other online resources (car gurus, Edmunds, etc.). I was skeptical due to many years of owning my delivery business and purchasing dozens of delivery vehicles over the past 17 years. I researched and compared similar vehicles in multiple cities and dealerships. It became very clear in a short amount of time that Shawn had the best selection, price, and professionalism available to my business. We spoke over the phone and he answered all of my questions, (which I had many), honestly and adeptly. I wasn't sure if I could afford all of the vehicles outright and he provided me with contact info for Jamie (@Cambridge capital), their in house financing. They too were patient and forthright with my needs. I explained to Shawn the need to expedite the vehicle sales (due to my rapid expansion), as well as the necessity of transport to my area in northern California. He worked with me to keep costs low as well as having my vans shipped to me in a very short period of time after the purchase of vehicles. Shawn was especially honest about the timeframe in which he could reasonably ship the vans to my business in Humboldt. He didn't want to promise something that he couldn't deliver on. It turns out that he found a reputable truck transporter in record time and had my vans delivered to me the next day (which just so happened to be a couple of days before I absolutely needed them). The Van's I bought were low miles, fleet maintained, government owned, and lacking in defects. The 2005 E350 Ford arrived with brand new tires and the 2006 Chevy Express 2500 had various aftermarket extras. Both vehicles were immaculately detailed and in perfect working order. So far so good mechanically, and I have been using them excessively during the holiday peak season rush. I will more than likely be expanding in the future and Shawn at Best Auto sales will be the person I call to purchase vehicles from. I can't say enough to Shawn's honesty, caring, attention to detail, efficiency, professionalism and dedication to providing me with quality vehicles. Thanks for being top notch and helping me with my business needs! I while heartedly reccomend Best Auto Sales for your commercial auto needs.<//Text><Time>1609210127192<//Time><Gmap_id>0x80dcc80381abcedd:0x33ce4e9eb538d68f</Gmap_id>< user_name>

< Review>
Listen. If all you base your business on is seafood and 75% of that is shrimp. And your charging premium for your food why not devain your shrimp.
I mean you use good quality shrimp why not process them correctly, reflecting on your price point. All the condiments are here including chile tepin sauce, tapatio, offbrand saltines and ketchup. Limes, salt.
The food itself is fresh and is made to order, so that's a great start. Service is good. They also take debit but not sure of surcharges.
Cleanliness is questionable. The card reader needs 2 minutes of attention to get back up and usable. The folding sign looks like it was ran over and just being put out anyways.
You might already have a clientele base but taking instagram/facebook pictures with filters and staging the food will only get you so far.
Again, the food is good
Especially if you don't care about the details.
I do, and can tell you that the pricing has to reflect in the final product.
This was just my opinion. Everyone reading this should try it yourself and make your own opinion on food details.
Take it to the next level you guy's.
But for reals though. Everyone on the team has to be on the same page or its not gonna change anything.

< review>
At the end of July 2020 I had a crown go bad and that resulted in my tooth needing to be pulled. A month after the extraction I was still having pain and random swelling. I was then bounced around by my dentist to various specialists. It wasn‚Äôt till November that I was told my jaw was infected and I was in far worst shape then I thought.

I was referred to Dr. Kheradpir and after making some hasty calls for approval and appointments his office was gracious enough to fit me in. The staff was phenomenal on getting us scheduled and making sure the urgency of my medical problem was addressed.

My wife accompanied me to my first visit and while our heads were still spinning from all the damage my mouth/jaw was in, we left that appointment feeling that whatever happened Dr. Kheradpir was in our corner and things would be ok.

He was able to tell me exactly what was happening and while it was a real tough situation, I remember him saying we will fix you. Those words meant a lot.

In a short period of time he was able to evaluate my condition and have a solid game plan that we began executing immediately. I have had one procedure so far; several checkups and things are finally better. I still have quite the road of recovery ahead of me but I know Dr. Kheradpir is the right person to get me put back together.

His staff is fantastic and they do a great job of making sure you feel comfortable while you are there. I don‚Äôt know how I would be if I had not been so fortunate to end up in their care.< /review>

< review>
Had to go in for a tooth extraction. I was a nervous wreck as ive had a terrible experience as a child so i avoid the dentist until i cant anymore. I had an 8am appt so parking was easy. Check in did not take long. I got called into the back fairly quickly by Alex or Aly, i couldnt remember her name, my toothache drowned out everything. She did go over the procedure, risks and all and help numbed the area. I almost opted for the gas but after talking it over, it wasnt necessary. Dr. Curiel performed the extraction. He made sure i was really numbed and the staff were helpful of reminding me to breath through my nose. The only slight pain i felt was the lidocaine injection. Otherwise, a little bit of pressure and the tooth was out. Im home now with a bit of swelling but the pain is gone. Im so glad they were able to squeeze me in and for the awesome service they provided me.<//review>

This is hands down the best dental office I have ever been to by far. The staff is super friendly and helpful. Doctor Alexander is very good at what he does. I highly recommend this office and Dr. K on several occasions.  First a little about me, I'm 79 years old and had a bad experiences as a young child with a dentist.  I have been known to get so nervous, that I left the office before I was seen. Dr K and his office staff were kind and understanding, even after I left his office on one occasion.  Dr. K has done  four implants for me and on each occasion has been completely honest with me as to what to expect after the procedure. He was compassionate and patient with me.   The last procedure I had done was three implants on my lower jaw.  I was told I could expect, bruising, swelling and discomfort.  I can honestly say I had know bruising, little to know swelling, and minor discomfort.  In all of my implants the procedure has taken the full nine months to a year because I had no bone and need to "grow bone".  I now do not have to wear a partial and each day I thank God for my dentist, Dr. Namdarian and Dr K , who together figure how to  do the impossible for me.< /review>

<Text>Being as stubborn as I am, I waited until my whole jaw was in complete pain till I called to make a wisdom tooth removal surgery. My first choice was supposed to be the same place that my brother went to, but they said the soonest they could see me was in a week, and at this point, I couldn't sleep and I cried a lot from so much pain. My dentist helped me out and called different oral surgery places and out of 5, this is the only one that said they can see me the next day. They usually open around 8 or so, but they open earlier for patients with an emergency. My appointment was at 6, but I got in much earlier than that. I was very nervous because I've never had surgery before, but the lady who helped me and Dr. Chien, were more than helpful and reassuring. We jokes, laughed, talked a lot about what is going to happen. I liked how they went over the process multiple times and assured me that things can happen, but they are always careful. They only give you enough medicine to get you to sleep, and the process in total takes about 20 mins. Your mouth feels numb after, but you don't get that drowsy high feeling from the medicine because they only give you a minimal dosage of it. I loved the staff, and Dr.Chien was awesome! Can't wait to see you all when you come eat Chinese breakfast at my work!<//Text>< Pictures>

< text>
I absolutely LOVED my experience here with Dr. Chien and his staff. I was dreading taking out all 4 of my wisdom teeth because my wife had a horrible experience a few years ago at another dentist (I thought she was going to die! Slight exaggeration but she was in a lot of pain and for quite some time) Originally, I visited two other dental offices but my "gut" feeling was telling me "No, not here". I understand there is a business side of things but in short, I felt like a piece of meat with $ signs attached. Thanks to the recommendation of Dr. Mirzayan, another passionate dentist, I was directed towards Dr. Chien and his staff. As a person who is very passionate about my career/life, I know passion when I see it and you could feel it with Dr. Chien. The bedside manners here were top-notched and you could tell people enjoyed working here. Lastly, I believe Dr. Chien did such a fine job with the extraction that there was no pain after the first day (Yes you read that correctly). I look back at my wife's experience and I feel truly blessed! I would give this rating 10 stars if I could and I've also thought of putting in an application to work here in the future should I consider a career change :D Apologies for the novel but I wanted to share my experiences and hopefully it may help others :)</text>
